<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:22PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN FRANKLIN AND
SOUTHEASTERN FULTON COUNTIES THROUGH 600 PM EDT...
At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Hancock, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mercersburg, Big Cove Tannery, Needmore, Claylick and Whitetail Ski
Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
